[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926927&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926927&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

OK, so... Is it "reasonable" to remember the SOA serial number, and when
an object's TTL expires, instead of requerying the object, requery the
SOA serial number of the zone, and if it hasn't changed, update the TTLs
(using some appropriate value) of all objects in the zone?  This is
based on the contrapositive of "If any object is changed, the SOA serial
number is changed" which is "If the SOA serial number hasn't changed, no
object has changed."

